        " \nUNIVERSITY OF MPUMALANGA\n ",
        " \n \nThe University of Mpumalanga (UMP) is a comprehensive University established to provide a relevant, engaged and sustainable learning and teaching environment of outstanding academic excellence to match not only the skills and economic needs of the Province and its people, but of the Country as a whole. The UMP invites applications for the following position/s.\n \nNGAP LECTURER: ISINDEBELE\n \nOrganisational Unit: University of Mpumalanga -> Teaching and Learning -> Office of the DVC Teaching and Learning\n \nJob Primary Purpose\nThe nGAP is positioned by the Department of Higher Education and Training as a prestigious programme in the sector, and candidates who demonstrate a passion for following a career as an academic and who have demonstrated high academic ability will be recruited.\n \nKey Performance Areas:\nPROGRAMME INFORMATION \nThe University of Mpumalanga invites applications for nGAP Lectureship in IsiNdebele.\nThis is a permanent post at the Lecturer level. Full details of the nGAP programme can be found at http://www.ssauf.dhet.gov.za/ngap.html and applicants are encouraged to carefully read the information on the website before applying.\nThe nGAP is positioned by the Department of Higher Education and Training as a prestigious programme in the sector, and candidates who demonstrate a passion for following a career as an academic and who have demonstrated high academic ability will be recruited.\n\nMinimum Requirements:\nApplicants must have at least a Master\u2019s qualification in an appropriate field of study.\nBe a South African Citizen.\nProspective candidates should have achieved an average of 70% or above in the preceding degree, which should be a minimum of a Master\u2019s degree.\nBe 40 years or younger.\nBe prepared and able to undertake and complete postgraduate studies at the doctoral level.\n \nKey Competencies\nSKILLS\nGood written and verbal communication skills.\nGood problem-solving skills.\nGood interpersonal skills.\n \nPersonal Attributes\nPeople orientated, hard worker, responsible, reliable, creative and innovative.\nRespectful, honesty, punctuality and understand of protocol.\nProven attributes of transparency, integrity and teamwork.\n \n \nAdvert Closing Date: 17/12/2023\n \nCandidates who meet the minimum requirements are invited to apply for the advertised position(s). Remuneration will be commensurate with the level of the position the incumbent is applying for.\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n ",
        " \n \n \n \n\nThe University of Mpumalanga (UMP) is a comprehensive University established to provide a relevant, engaged and sustainable learning and teaching environment of outstanding academic excellence to match not only the skills and economic needs of the Province and its people, but of the Country as a whole. The UMP invites applications for the following position/s.\n \nNGAP LECTURER: INFORMATION COMMUNICATION TECHNOLOGY\n \nOrganisational Unit: University of Mpumalanga -> Teaching and Learning -> Office of the DVC Teaching and Learning\n \nJob Primary Purpose\nThe nGAP is positioned by the Department of Higher Education and Training as a prestigious programme in the sector, and candidates who demonstrate a passion for following a career as an academic and who have demonstrated high academic ability will be recruited.\n \nKey Performance Areas:\nPROGRAMME INFORMATION \nThe University of Mpumalanga invites applications for nGAP Lectureship in Sociology.\nThis is a permanent post at the Lecturer level. Full details of the nGAP programme can be found at http://www.ssauf.dhet.gov.za/ngap.html and applicants are encouraged to carefully read the information on the website before applying.\nThe nGAP is positioned by the Department of Higher Education and Training as a prestigious programme in the sector, and candidates who demonstrate a passion for following a career as an academic and who have demonstrated high academic ability will be recruited.\n\nMinimum Requirements:\nApplicants must have at least a Master\u2019s qualification in an appropriate field of study.\nBe a South African Citizen.\nProspective candidates should have achieved an average of 70% or above in the preceding degree, which should be a minimum of a Master\u2019s degree.\nBe 40 years or younger.\nBe prepared and able to undertake and complete postgraduate studies at the doctoral level.\n \nKey Competencies\nSKILLS\nGood written and verbal communication skills.\nGood problem-solving skills.\nGood interpersonal skills.\n \nPersonal Attributes\nPeople orientated, hard worker, responsible, reliable, creative and innovative.\nRespectful, honesty, punctuality and understand of protocol.\nProven attributes of transparency, integrity and teamwork.\n \n \nAdvert Closing Date: 17/12/2023\n \nCandidates who meet the minimum requirements are invited to apply for the advertised position(s). Remuneration will be commensurate with the level of the position the incumbent is applying for.\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n\n \n \n ",
        " \n \n \n \nThe University of Mpumalanga (UMP) is a comprehensive University established to provide a relevant, engaged and sustainable learning and teaching environment of outstanding academic excellence to match not only the skills and economic needs of the Province and its people, but of the Country as a whole. The UMP invites applications for the following position/s.\n \nNGAP LECTURER: ENGLISH LANGUAGE & LITERATURE\n \nOrganisational Unit: University of Mpumalanga -> Teaching and Learning -> Office of the DVC Teaching and Learning\n \nJob Primary Purpose\nThe nGAP is positioned by the Department of Higher Education and Training as a prestigious programme in the sector, and candidates who demonstrate a passion for following a career as an academic and who have demonstrated high academic ability will be recruited.\n \nKey Performance Areas:\nPROGRAMME INFORMATION \nThe University of Mpumalanga invites applications for nGAP Lectureship in Sociology.\nThis is a permanent post at the Lecturer level. Full details of the nGAP programme can be found at http://www.ssauf.dhet.gov.za/ngap.html and applicants are encouraged to carefully read the information on the website before applying.\nThe nGAP is positioned by the Department of Higher Education and Training as a prestigious programme in the sector, and candidates who demonstrate a passion for following a career as an academic and who have demonstrated high academic ability will be recruited.\n \nMinimum Requirements:\nApplicants must have at least a Master\u2019s qualification in an appropriate field of study.\nBe a South African Citizen.\nProspective candidates should have achieved an average of 70% or above in the preceding degree, which should be a minimum of a Master\u2019s degree.\nBe 40 years or younger.\nBe prepared and able to undertake and complete postgraduate studies at the doctoral level.\n \nKey Competencies\nSKILLS\nGood written and verbal communication skills.\nGood problem-solving skills.\nGood interpersonal skills.\n \nPersonal Attributes\nPeople orientated, hard worker, responsible, reliable, creative and innovative.\nRespectful, honesty, punctuality and understand of protocol.\nProven attributes of transparency, integrity and teamwork.\n \nAdvert Closing Date: 17/12/2023\n \nCandidates who meet the minimum requirements are invited to apply for the advertised position(s). Remuneration will be commensurate with the level of the position the incumbent is applying for.\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n ",
        " \n \n \n \nThe University of Mpumalanga (UMP) is a comprehensive University established to provide a relevant, engaged and sustainable learning and teaching environment of outstanding academic excellence to match not only the skills and economic needs of the Province and its people, but of the Country as a whole. The UMP invites applications for the following position/s.\n \nLECTURER IN TOURISM MANAGEMENT\n \nOrganisational Unit: University of Mpumalanga -> Teaching and Learning -> Faculty of Economics, Development and Business Sciences\n \nJob Primary Purpose\nThe primary role of this position is to provide teaching and learning, research, Engagement, Leadership and Administration of the Tourism modules.\n \nKey Performance Areas:\nLeadership\nThe provision of some leadership at the module level.\nTeaching and Learning\nProvision of theoretically informed and pedagogically sound teaching.\nResearch\nResearch and the production of accredited research outputs.\nEngagement  \nEngagement, through which knowledge and skills are used to benefit the discipline/profession and the community.\n \nMinimum Requirements:\nHighest qualification\nMaster's qualification in Tourism Management with undergraduate degree in Tourism Management.   \nPreferably a Doctoral qualification or progress towards a Doctoral qualification in Tourism Management.\nTeaching experience  Some experience with the facilitation of learning, possibly as a Tutor and preferably some teaching experience.\nResearch\nSome evidence of research activity such as published papers or conference attendance, which may be associated with postgraduate research.\nEngagement\nPreference will be given to applicants who have some experience with engagement activities.\n \nKey Competencies\nDisciplinary knowledge\nIn-depth knowledge in the theory and application of the discipline of Tourism Management.\nLeadership\nGood interpersonal skills including communication skills.\nTeaching and Learning\nAn appreciation of modern theories of teaching and learning in higher education and some skills as a Tutor or Mentor.\nResearch\nSome research skills.\nEngagement\nAn understanding of the role of the University in Engagement.\n \nPersonal Attributes\nPeople orientated, hard worker, responsible, reliable, creative and innovative.\nRespectful, honest, punctual and understand protocol.\nProven attributes of transparency, integrity and teamwork.\n \nAdvert Closing Date: 17/12/2023\n \nCandidates who meet the minimum requirements are invited to apply for the advertised position(s). Remuneration will be commensurate with the level of the position the incumbent is applying for.\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n ",
        " \n \n \n \nThe University of Mpumalanga (UMP) is a comprehensive University established to provide a relevant, engaged and sustainable learning and teaching environment of outstanding academic excellence to match not only the skills and economic needs of the Province and its people, but of the Country as a whole. The UMP invites applications for the following position/s.\n \nDIRECTOR RESEARCH MANAGEMENT\n \nOrganisational Unit: University of Mpumalanga -> Research Innovation & Internationalisation -> Office of the DVC: RII\n \nJob Primary Purpose\nThe primary purpose of the role is to develop and direct strategies in support of research and innovation, research funding and research capacity development of the University. The incumbent in the role interacts with national and international research funding, standards-setting, regulatory, and policy institutions to grow the University\u2019s research and innovation portfolio in a sustainable and impactful way. The incumbent will also be responsible to spearhead initiatives aimed at repositioning the University as a research-active institution whose work shapes futures in support of the vision, mission, values and strategic priorities of the University.\n \nKey Performance Areas:\nTo direct, manage and facilitate an increase in accredited research outputs.\nTo direct, manage and facilitate the provision of capacity development initiatives to research staff and postgraduate students. \nTo manage and facilitate research funding and postgraduate bursaries. \nStrategic growth and effectiveness of the Research Office, including initial advancement of an innovation focus.  \nStrategic research partnership management.\nResearch communication.\nFinancial and physical resources optimisation.\n \nMinimum Requirements:\nA PhD in A relevant area of specialisation.\nAt least 10 years\u2019 relevant experience in a senior or executive position in an academic institution or research organisation.\nAcademic/research leadership and management experience will be an advantage.\nProven experience in dealing with national and international research funding agencies.\n \nKey Competencies\nChange leadership and transformation.\nWell-developed communication skills.\nStrategic and lateral thinking.\nComplex problem solving skills.\nAbility to function at policy and senior levels of management.\nExcellent People Management skills.\nDemonstrated track record managing research development-focused portfolios.\nKnowledge of the South African Higher Education and Science Sectors.\n\nPersonal Attributes\nPeople orientated, hard worker, responsible, reliable, creative and innovative.\nRespect, honest, punctual and understand protocol.\nProven attributes of transparency, integrity and teamwork.\n \nAdvert Closing Date: 17/12/2023\n \nCandidates who meet the minimum requirements are invited to apply for the advertised position(s). Remuneration will be commensurate with the level of the position the incumbent is applying for.\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n ",
        " \n \n \n \n\nThe University of Mpumalanga (UMP) is a comprehensive University established to provide a relevant, engaged and sustainable learning and teaching environment of outstanding academic excellence to match not only the skills and economic needs of the Province and its people, but of the Country as a whole. The UMP invites applications for the following position/s.\n \nDIRECTOR: ACADEMIC SUPPORT SERVICES (P5)\nOrganisational Unit: University of Mpumalanga -> Teaching and Learning -> Academic Support Services\n \nJob Primary Purpose\nThe primary purpose of this position is to direct the development and implementation of programmes to advance the academic project through the provision of academic support services to enhance student access with success.\n \nKey Performance Areas:\nActively support the DVC: Teaching and Learning and Faculties in the leadership and management of the academic projects.\nDirect the development, implementation and review of the institution's Teaching, Learning and Assessment Strategy.\nDirect the induction of academic staff.\nDevelop and implement sound approaches of academic staff professional development.\nDevelop and oversee the implementation of student access support initiatives.\nDevelop and implement approaches to technology-enabled teaching and learning.\nEstablish track record of relevant research in teaching and learning theory and practice.\nEngage effectively with relevant external stakeholders and professional bodies such as DHET, CHE, HELTASA, etc.\nManagement of the University Capacity Development Programme and other teaching related grants and strategic projects.\n \nMinimum Requirements:\nA Doctoral Degree in Education or an equivalent qualification in a related area of specialisation.\nAt least 10 years of experience in the academic support of teaching and learning within the higher education environment with at leave five years in a management role.\nKnowledge of the South Africa Higher Education Sector specifically in the areas of academic support and teaching and learning.\nTrack record of academic publications in academic support of teaching and learning.\nConsiderable relevant experience working with the DHET, CHE, HEQC and relevant partners.\n \nKey Competencies\nKNOWLEDGE \nAn excellent understanding of the theory and practice of teaching and learning in higher education in South Africa and more widely.\nA sound understanding of Higher Education and its roles in South Africa.\n \nSKILLS \nWell-developed interpersonal and leadership skills.\nExcellent written and oral skills.\nPresentation skills.\n \nPersonal Attributes\nPeople orientated, hard worker, responsible, reliable, creative and innovation.\nRespectful, honest, punctual and understand protocol.\nProven attributes of transparency, integrity and teamwork.\n \nAdvert Closing Date: 17/12/2023\n \nCandidates who meet the minimum requirements are invited to apply for the advertised position(s). Remuneration will be commensurate with the level of the position the incumbent is applying for.\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n ",
        " \n \n \n \nThe University of Mpumalanga (UMP) is a comprehensive University established to provide a relevant, engaged and sustainable learning and teaching environment of outstanding academic excellence to match not only the skills and economic needs of the Province and its people, but of the Country as a whole. The UMP invites applications for the following position/s.\n \nSENIOR LECTURER IN HOSPITALITY (2 X POSTS)\nOrganisational Unit: University of Mpumalanga -> Teaching and Learning -> Faculty of Economics, Development and Business Sciences\n \nJob Primary Purpose\nThe primary role of this position is to provide teaching, research and leadership in the School of Hospitality and Tourism Management.\n \nKey Performance Areas:\nKPAs  \nSenior Lecturer\nLeadership\nThe provision of leadership at the discipline level.\nTeaching & Learning\nProvision of theoretically informed and pedagogically sound teaching at undergraduate and postgraduate level.\nResearch      \nResearch and the production of accredited research outputs.\nPostgraduate supervision and the graduation of Masters' and Doctoral students in the minimum time.\nEngagement\nEngagement, through which knowledge and skills are used to benefit the discipline/profession and the community.\n \nMinimum Requirements:\nSenior Lecturer\nQualifications\nPhD in Tourism and Hospitality Management or relevant field.\nUndergraduate qualification in Hospitality Management or any Hospitality related discipline.\nTeaching experience\n5 years teaching experience in a variety of hospitality modules at university level.\nResearch\nA strong record of research outputs including papers in accredited national and international journals and presentations at national and international conferences.\nA good record of postgraduate supervision at Masters' level with some of these students publishing their research.\nEngagement  \nParticipation in learned societies.\nSome application of disciplinary/professional knowledge and skills to the benefit of the external community.\n \nKey Competencies\nCompetencies and skills.\nSenior Lecturer\nDisciplinary knowledge\nIn depth knowledge in the theory and application of the Hospitality discipline\nLeadership\nGood understanding of principles of leadership and management with well-developed leadership and management skills.\nGood interpersonal skills including communication skills\nTeaching and Learning        \nSound understanding of modern theories of teaching and learning in Higher Education and well-developed teaching skills.\nAbility to teach online.\nResearch\nWell-developed quantitative and/or qualitative research methodology skills.\nEngagement\nGood understanding of the role of the University in Engagement.\n \nPersonal Attributes\nPeople orientated, hard worker, responsible, reliable, creative and innovative.\nRespectful, honesty, punctuality and understand of protocol.\nProven attributes of transparency, integrity and teamwork.\n \n \nAdvert Closing Date: 17/12/2023\n \nCandidates who meet the minimum requirements are invited to apply for the advertised position(s). Remuneration will be commensurate with the level of the position the incumbent is applying for.\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n ",
        " \n \n \n \n\nThe University of Mpumalanga (UMP) is a comprehensive University established to provide a relevant, engaged and sustainable learning and teaching environment of outstanding academic excellence to match not only the skills and economic needs of the Province and its people, but of the Country as a whole. The UMP invites applications for the following position/s.\n \nTECHNICAL OFFICER IN CULINARY ARTS\nOrganisational Unit University of Mpumalanga -> Teaching and Learning -> Faculty of Economics, Development and Business Sciences\n \nJob Primary Purpose\nThe primary purpose of the role is to assist the Culinary Studies and Nutrition Lecturer to administer practical classes in Hospitality. The incumbent will also assist the lecturer in providing instructional lectures in simulated kitchens, as well as lead hands-on instruction sessions through a practical training program.\n \nKey Performance Areas:\nProvision of technical support for kitchen practical training.\nSupervision, enforcing student discipline and transferring of skills in the training kitchen.\nMaintaining current and accurate records for all culinary practical recipes.\nPlanning and execution of practical assessments where applicable.\nEngagement through which knowledge and skills are used to benefit the culinary profession/discipline and the community.\n \nMinimum Requirements:\nM+3 year Hospitality qualification in Culinary Arts/Professional Cookery or any Culinary related qualification.\nSpecialised Chef/Culinary knowledge.\nAt least five (5) years' experience as a Chef/Culinary Manager, of which three years' (3) experience should be in a training kitchen as an instructor in an institution of higher learning.  \nSome experience in mentoring of students and facilitation of practical classes in training kitchens.\n \nKey Competencies\nA high degree of technical ability to relay information in a manner that provides a positive learning experience and instils a passion for the chefs' profession.\nKnowledge and technical skills in the form of mastery of cooking and banking principles and techniques.\nAn appreciation of modern methods of cooking and theories of teaching and learning in Higher Education and some skills as a chefs instructor.\nDemonstrated competency in a range of techniques and procedures associated with scientific practical classes.\nTraining of students, enforcing discipline and transferring of skills.\nKnowledge and experience of hybrid models of teaching and learning (face-to-face and online).\n \nPersonal Attributes\nPeople orientated, hard worker, responsible, reliable, creative and innovative.\nRespectful, honest, punctual and understand protocol.\nProven attributes of transparency, integrity and teamwork.\nConceptual ability, conflict management and mentoring ability.\nChef related competency skills.\n \nSKILLS\nDelegate responsibility to students.\nChef related competency skills.\nConflict management and mentoring ability.\nContinuous learning inclination.\nGood verbal and written communication skills.\nPresentation skills.\nTraining and coaching skills.\nQuality orientation and good work standards.\nComputer skills.\n \nAdvert Closing Date: 17/12/2023\n \nCandidates who meet the minimum requirements are invited to apply for the advertised position(s). Remuneration will be commensurate with the level of the position the incumbent is applying for.\n\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n ",
        " \n \n \n \nThe University of Mpumalanga (UMP) is a comprehensive University established to provide a relevant, engaged and sustainable learning and teaching environment of outstanding academic excellence to match not only the skills and economic needs of the Province and its people, but of the Country as a whole. The UMP invites applications for the following position/s.\n \nLECTURER IN CULINARY ARTS\nOrganisational Unit: University of Mpumalanga -> Teaching and Learning -> Faculty of Economics, Development and Business Sciences\n \nJob Primary Purpose\nThe primary role of this position is to provide teaching, research and leadership in Culinary Arts.\n \nKey Performance Areas:\nKPAs\nLecturer\nLeadership\nThe provision of some leadership at the module level.\nTeaching & Learning\nProvision of theoretically informed and pedagogically sound teaching of hospitality.\nResearch\nResearch and the production of accredited research outputs.\nPostgraduate supervision leading to the graduation of Master's students in the minimum time.\nEngagement\nEngagement, through which knowledge and skills are used to benefit the discipline/profession and the community.\n \nMinimum Requirements:\nLecturer\nQualifications\nMaster's qualification and preferably a Doctoral qualification or progress towards a Doctoral qualification in Hospitality Management of related.\nUndergraduate qualification in hospitality/professional cookery/culinary arts.\nTeaching experience\nSome experience with the facilitation of learning, possibly as a tutor and preferably some teaching experience.\nResearch\nSome evidence of research activity such as published papers or conference attendance, which may be associated with postgraduate research.\nEngagement\nPreference will be given to applicants who have some experience with engagement activities.\n \nKey Competencies\nCompetencies and skills\nLecturer\nDisciplinary knowledge\nA sound knowledge of the theory and application of the discipline.\nLeadership\nGood interpersonal skills including communication skills.\nTeaching & Learning  \nAn appreciation of modern theories of teaching and learning in Higher Education and some skills as a tutor or mentor. \nAbility to teach online.\nResearch\nSome research skills.\nEngagement\nAn understanding of the role of Universities in Engagement.\n \nPersonal Attributes\nPeople orientated, hard worker, responsible, reliable, creative and innovative.\nRespectful, honest, punctual and understand protocol.\nProven attributes of transparency, integrity and teamwork.\n \nAdvert Closing Date: 17/12/2023\n \nCandidates who meet the minimum requirements are invited to apply for the advertised position(s). Remuneration will be commensurate with the level of the position the incumbent is applying for.\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n \n ",
        " \n \n \n \nThe University of Mpumalanga (UMP) is a comprehensive University established to provide a relevant, engaged and sustainable learning and teaching environment of outstanding academic excellence to match not only the skills and economic needs of the Province and its people, but of the Country as a whole. The UMP invites applications for the following position/s.\n \nLECTURER IN ENGLISH\nOrganisational Unit: University of Mpumalanga -> Teaching and Learning -> Faculty of Economics, Development and Business Sciences\n \nJob Primary Purpose\nThe primary role of this position is to provide teaching, research and leadership in English.\n \nKey Performance Areas:\nKPAs  \nLecturer\nLeadership\nThe provision of some leadership at the module level.\nTeaching & Learning\nProvision of theoretically informed and pedagogically sound teaching of English.\nResearch\nResearch and the production of accredited research outputs. \nEngagement\nEngagement, through which knowledge and skills are used to benefit the discipline/profession and the community. \n \nMinimum Requirements:\nLecturer\nLeadership\nMaster's qualification in English and preferably a Doctoral qualification or progress towards a Doctoral qualification in English.\nTeaching & Learning\nSome experience with the facilitation of learning, possible as a tutor and preferably some teaching experience.\nResearch\nSome evidence of research activity such as published papers or conference attendance, which may be associated with postgraduate research.\nEngagement\nPreference will be given to applicants who have some experience with engagement activities.\n \nKey Competencies\nCompetencies and skills\nLecturer\nDisciplinary knowledge\nA sound knowledge of the theory and application of the discipline.\nLeadership\nGood interpersonal skills including communication skills.\nTeaching & Learning  \nAn appreciation of modern theories of teaching and learning in Higher Education and some skills as a tutor or mentor.\nAbility to teach online.\nResearch\nSome research skills.\nEngagement\nAn understanding of the role of Universities in Engagement.\n \nPersonal Attributes\nPeople orientated, hard worker, responsible, reliable, creative and innovative.\nRespectful, honest, punctual and understand protocol.\nProven attributes of transparency, integrity and teamwork.\n \nAdvert Closing Date: 17/12/2023\nCandidates who meet the minimum requirements are invited to apply for the advertised position(s). Remuneration will be commensurate with the level of the position the incumbent is applying for.\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE\n \n \n ",
        "The University of Mpumalanga (UMP) is a comprehensive University established to provide a relevant, engaged and sustainable learning and teaching environment of outstanding academic excellence to match not only the skills and economic needs of the Province and its people, but of the Country as a whole. The UMP invites applications for the following position/s.\n \nSENIOR LECTURER/LECTURER IN LAW (X3 POSITIONS)\nOrganisational Unit: University of Mpumalanga -> Teaching and Learning -> Faculty of Economics, Development and Business Sciences\nJob Primary Purpose\nTo teach law modules, conduct research, participate in community engagement and provide leadership at discipline level (Senior Lecturer)/module level (Lecturer).\n \nKey Performance Areas:\nKPAs  \nSenior Lecturer - Lecturer\nLeadership\nThe provision of leadership at discipline level.\nThe provision of some leadership at module level.\nTeaching & Learning\nProvision of theoretically informed and pedagogically sound teaching of Law modules.\nProvision of theoretically informed and pedagogically sound teaching in the field of Law\nResearch\nA strong record of research outputs including papers in accredited national and international journals and presentations at national and international conference.\nA good record of postgraduate supervision at Masters' level leading to the graduation of Masters' students in the minimum time.\nSome evidence of research activities such as post-graduate supervision (at least at honours level), published papers of conference attendance.\nEngagement\nParticipation in learned societies.\nEngagement, through which knowledge and skills are used to benefit the discipline/ profession and the community.\nSome evidence of engagement activities, through which knowledge and skills are used to benefit the discipline/profession and the community.\n \nMinimum Requirements:\nMinimum requirements\nSenior Lecturer - Lecturer\n \nHighest qualification\nA Doctoral qualification in Law (LL.D or Ph.D). Admission as an Attorney or an Advocate of the High Court will be an advantaged.\nA Master of Laws and preferably a Doctoral qualification in Law (LL.D or Ph.D). Admission as an Attorney or an Advocate of the High Court will be an added advantage.   \nTeaching experience\nAt lease 5 years of teaching experience at University level in the field of Law. \n\nSome experience with the facilitation of learning, possible as a tutor and preferably some teaching experience .\nResearch\nA strong record of research outputs including publication in accredited national and International journals and presentations at national and international conferences.\n \nA good record of postgraduate supervision at Masters\u2019 level with some of these students publishing their research.\nSome evidence of research activities such as published papers or conference attendance, which may be associated with postgraduate research.\nEngagement\nEvidence of engagement, through which knowledge and skills are used to benefit the discipline/profession and the community. \nSome experience with engagement activities\n \nKey Competencies\nCompetencies and Skills\nSenior Lecturer - Lecturer\nDisciplinary knowledge\nIn-depth knowledge of the theory and application of the discipline.  A sound knowledge of Law of Insolvency, Law of Evidence, Banking Law, Law of Delict, Constitution and Statutory Interpretation, Legal philosophy, Research Methodology and Law of Succession.    A sound knowledge of the theory and application of the discipline.  A sound knowledge of Law of Insolvency, Law of Evidence, Banking Law, Law of Delict, Constitution and Statutory Interpretation, Legal philosophy, Research Methodology and Law of Succession.\nLeadership    \nGood understanding of the principles of leadership and management with well-developed leadership and management skills.   Good interpersonal skills including communication skills.\nTeaching & Learning  \nSound understanding of modern theories of teaching and learning in Higher Education and well-developed teaching skills.\nAn appreciation of modern theories of teaching and learning in Higher Education and some skills as a tutor or mentor.\nResearch\nWell-developed research skills.\nSome research skills.\n \nEngagement  \nGood understanding of the role of Universities in Engagement.\nEngagement, through which knowledge and skills are used to benefit the discipline/profession and the community.\nAn understanding of the role of Universities in Engagement.\n \nPersonal Attributes\nPeople orientated, hard worker, responsible, reliable, creative and innovative.\nRespectful, honest, punctual and understand protocol.\nProven attributes of transparency, integrity and teamwork.\nGood interpersonal skills including communication skills.\n \nAdvert Closing Date: 17/12/2023\n \nCandidates who meet the minimum requirements are invited to apply for the advertised position(s). Remuneration will be commensurate with the level of the position the incumbent is applying for.\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE",
        "The University of Mpumalanga (UMP) is a comprehensive University established to provide a relevant, engaged and sustainable learning and teaching environment of outstanding academic excellence to match not only the skills and economic needs of the Province and its people, but of the Country as a whole. The UMP invites applications for the following position/s.\n \nNETWORK ADMINISTRATOR\nOrganisational Unit: University of Mpumalanga -> Information & Communication Technology (ICT) -> ICT Operations\n \nJob Primary Purpose\nThe primary role of this position is to maintain the local area network (LAN), wide area network (WAN), Wi-Fi and other Internet resources to ensure that the University \u2018s network is available, operating efficiently and securely throughout.\n \nKey Performance Areas:\nThe ability to adapt to changing circumstances.\nKnowledge of Cisco WLC, FortiEDR, FortiMail, and FortiGate Firewalls.\nKnowledge of CiscoIdentity Services Engine (ISE) & TACACS.\nEnterprise-scale LAN systems (STP, VTP, Port-Channel, Trunking, VLANs, VACL's, Stacking)\nUnderstanding Protocols such as (HTTP/S, DHCP, DNS, SMTP, SNMP, NTP, SSH, FTH, and other web-based protocols) and routing protocols (EIGRP & OSPF)\nKnowledge and practical understanding of wiring cabinets (patch panels, Cat 6, Cisco switch technology)\nWorking knowledge of intrusion detection and prevention techniques. \nKnowledge of CCTV, Access Control systems.\nKnowledge of and experience in a multi-campus environment.\n \nMinimum Requirements:\nM+3   Bachelor\u2019s degree in Computer Science/ICT/IT or relevant qualification.\nCisco Certified Network Associate (CCNA) or Cisco Certified Network Professional (CCNP)\n.CCIE certification would be an added advantage.\nNSE certification from 4 \u2013 8 would be an added advantage.\n.ITIL Certification would be an added advantage.\nMicrosoft Azure cloud experience an advantage.\nAt least 6 years\u2019 relevant network enterprise working experience.\n \nKey Competencies\nKNOWLEDGE\nThe ability to adapt to changing circumstances.\nKnowledge of Cisco WLC, FortiEDR, FortiMail, and FortiGate Firewalls.\nKnowledge of Cisco Identity Services Engine (ISE) & TACACS.\nEnterprise-scale LAN systems (STP, VTP, Port-channel, Trunking, VLANs, VACL\u2019s,Stacking).\nUnderstanding Protocols such as (HTTP/S, DHCP, DNS, SMTP, SNMP, NTP, SSH,FTP, and other web-based protocols) and routing protocols (EIGRP & OSPF).\nKnowledge and practical understanding of wiring cabinets (patch panels, Cat 6,Cisco switching technology).Working knowledge of intrusion detection and prevention techniques.\nKnowledge of CCTV and Access Control systems.\nKnowledge of and experience in a multi-campus environment.\nSKILLS\nGood written and verbal communication skills.\nGood problem solving skills.\nGood interpersonal skills.\nGood organising, planning and administration skills.\nGood time management skills.\nGood numerical skills.\n\nPersonal Attributes\nPeople orientated, hard worker, responsible, reliable, creative and innovative.\nRespect, honest, punctual and understand protocol.\nProven attributes of transparency, integrity and teamwork.\n \nAdvert Closing Date: 17/12/2023\n \nCandidates who meet the minimum requirements are invited to apply for the advertised position(s). Remuneration will be commensurate with the level of the position the incumbent is applying for.\n \nPLEASE APPLY HERE"
