        " \n \nMANAGEMENT ASSISTANT TRAINEE - BOKSBURG CAMPUS\nPost Designation:\nManagement Assistant Trainee\nReference:\nBok/10/2023\n \nPost Description:\nAssisting in all administration and office tasks and duties as assigned including:\nReceiving telephone calls;\nRendering customer service;\nInformation processing (memoranda, letters, e-mail, internet, minutes, etc.);\nFiling of documentation and records;\nCollection of post/faxes and distribution to relevant staff as required;\nData capturing;\nAssisting with registration of students;\nITS capturing.\n \nMinimum Requirements:\nN6 Management Assistant.\n \nNature of Appointment:\n18 Months.\n \nStipend:\nR4000 per month (stipend).\n \nClosing Date for Applications:\n12 December 2023 (16h00).\n \nDate of Commencement:\nAs soon as possible.\n \nEnquiries:\nMs MG Ngoetjana 063 970 3790\n \nCandidates are to complete and submit by hand: \nA NEW Z83 form (effective from 01 January 2021 - those who use the old Z83 form will be disqualified), obtainable from any Public Service Department, or here: Z83: Application for Employment;\nCurriculum Vitae, including at least three (3) contactable references, with email addresses;\nOriginal certified copies of academic record (transcript);\nOriginal certified copies lof Matric Certificate and Certificates N4-N6;\nOriginal certified copy of Identity Document, both sides;\n \n Applications should be hand delivered to Ekurhuleni West TVET College, Boksburg Campus, 49 North Street, Plantation, Boksburg 1460.\n \nPlease mark the application with the post title and reference number. Communication will only be entered into with shortlisted candidates and successful applicants.\n \nApplicants should kindly note that if the notice of appointment has not been received within 60 days of the closing date, it must be assumed that the application has been unsuccessful.\n \nIf you have previously completed your eighteen month internship, please do not apply.\n \nEKURHULENI WEST COLLEGE IS AN EQUAL OPPORTUNITIES EMPLOYER. THE COLLEGE RESERVES THE RIGHT NOT TO FILL THE POST.\n \n \n \n ",
        "POST LEVEL 1 LECTURER (PERMANENT) - ENGINEERING STUDIES - BOKSBURG CAMPUS\nEKURHULENI WEST TVET COLLEGE INVITES QUALIFIED AND EXPERIENCED CANDIDATES TO APPLY FOR THE\nFOLLOWING VACANCY TO BE FILLED ACCORDING TO THE CET ACT NO. 16 OF 2006 AS AMENDED.\n \nPost Designation:\nPost Level 1 Lecturer Permanent (Engineering Studies)\nReference Number:\nEWC/BOK/08/2023.\n \nMinimum Salary:\nR244 844 \u2013 R318 648 per Annum, plus benefits.\n \nEducational Requirements:\nA National Senior Certificate (Matric);\nNational Diploma in Information Technology, or equivalent;\nTVET Education Lecturing Qualification.\n \nMinimum Requirements:\nA minimum of zero to two (0-2) year's experience in the TVET Sector;\nRegistered with South African Council for Educators (SACE);\nModerator and Assessor certificate will be an added advantage;\nDriver's licence will be an added advantage.\n \nPost Description:\nPrinciples of Computer Programming L3;\nIntroduction to System Development L2-L4;\nIntroduction to Information Systems L2-L4;\nSystems Analysis and Design L3-L4;\nComputer Programming L4.\n \nDuties:\nEngage in learning / facilitating as per workload;\nAssess and record the performance of students;\nManage a learning program;\nDevelop the policy for the program;\nProvide guidance on the latest developments on approaches to the program;\n \nClosing Date For Applications:\n12 December 2023 (Tuesday)at 16h00;\nApplications received after the closing date will not be accepted.\n \nEnquiries:\nKindly contact the Human Resource Department - Ms MG Ngoetjana 063 970 3719.\n \nCandidates Are Required To Submit The Following Documents:\nA NEW Z83: Application for Employment Form, effective from 01 January 2021 (those who use the old Z83 will be disqualified), obtainable from any Public Service Department, or here: Z83: Application for Employment Form;\nA comprehensive CV with three (3) contactable references, with email addresses;\nOriginal certified copy of SACE Certificate;\nOriginal certified copies of qualifications (evaluated by DHET and SAQA, if foreign);\nOriginal certified copies of academic record/transcript;\nOriginal certified copy of driver's licence (front and back);\nOriginal certified copy of identity document (back and front, if a card).\n \nShortlisted candidates will go through a vetting process (citizenship, criminal check, verification of qualifications, social media, and credit check).\n \nApplications should be posted or hand delivered to Ekurhuleni West TVET College (Boksburg Campus), 49 North Street, Plantation 1460.\n\n \nPlease mark the application with the post title and reference number.\n \nMales across all races and white females and people with disabilities are highly encouraged to apply for this position in line with the Ekurhuleni West TVET College Employment Equity targets.\n \nCorrespondence will be entered into with short-listed candidates and the successful applicants. Applicants should kindly note that if no notice of appointment has been received within 30 days of the closing date, it must be assumed that the application has been unsuccessful.\n \nPeople with disabilities are encouraged to apply.\n \nEKURHULENI WEST COLLEGE IS AN EQUAL OPPORTUNITIES EMPLOYER. THE COLLEGE RESERVES THE RIGHT NOT TO FILL THE POST.",
        "MANAGEMENT ASSISTANT TRAINEE - KEMPTON CAMPUS\nPost Designation:\nManagement Assistant Trainee.\nReference:\nKEMP/05/2023.\n \nPost Description:\nManagement Assistant - assisting in all administration and office tasks and duties as assigned, including:\nReceiving telephone calls;\nRendering customer service;\nInformation processing (memoranda, letters, e-mail, internet, minutes, etc.);\nFiling of documentation and records;\nCollection of post/faxes and distribution to relevant staff, as required;\nData capturing;\nRegistration of students;\nITS capturing.\n \nMinimum requirements:\nN6 Management Assistant.\n \nNature of appointment:\n18 Months.\n \nStipend:\nR 4,000.00 per month (stipend).\n \nClosing date for applications:\n07 December 2023, (16h00).\n \nDate of commencement:\nAs soon as possible.\n \nEnquiries:\nMs SM Mariri / Ms ME Ntlemo (Human Resource Department), tel. 010 023 3691 x 2036.\n \nCandidates are to complete and submit by hand:\nA NEW Z83: Application for Employment form (effective from 01 January 2021 - those who use the old Z83 form will be disqualified) , and obtainable from any Public Service Department, or here: Z83: Application for Employment Form).\nCurriculum Vitae, including at least 3 contactable references, with email addresses;\nOriginal certified copies of academic record (transcript);\nOriginal certified copies of Matric certificate and Certificates for N4-N6;\nOriginal certified copy of Identity Document, both sides.\n \nApplications should be hand-delivered to Ekurhuleni West College, Kempton Campus, Cnr. Partridge Avenue & Pretoria Road, Kempton Park 1620.\n \nPlease mark the application with the post title and reference number. Communication will only be entered into with short-listed candidates and successful applicants.\n \nApplicants should kindly note that if a notice of appointment has not been received within 60 days of the closing date, it must be assumed that the application has been unsuccessful.\n \nIf you have previously completed your 18 months internship, please do not apply.\n \nEKURHULENI WEST COLLEGE IS AN EQUAL OPPORTUNITIES EMPLOYER. THE COLLEGE RESERVES THE RIGHT NOT TO FILL THE POST."
