        " \n \n \n \nLEGAL ADVISOR\nNational\nPermanent\n \nDescription\nPOSITION OBJECTIVE\nThe incumbent will provide input in the development of and help implement a Legal strategy and to assist with the provision of legal services to the business, including litigation management, contract vetting, drafting of legal documentation, etc.\n \nMINIMUM REQUIREMENTS\nAn LLB degree or equivalent qualification.\nAt least five years\u2019 experience, preferably within the public sector or exposure to public sector advisory in a firm of attorneys.\nMust be an Admitted Attorney/Advocate.\n \nTECHNICAL COMPETENCIES\nKnowledge and understanding of the local governmental landscape, and the regulatory and legislative operating environment.\nKnowledge and understanding of engineering-specific legislation with which SANRAL must comply, especially the FIDIC suite of contracts.\n \nKnowledge and understanding of a wide scope of legislation which includes but is not limited to:\nPreferential Procurement Policy Framework Act,\nPublic Finance Management Act,\nSouth African National Roads Agency SOC Limited and National Roads Act,\nNational Treasury\u2019s Regulations,\nConstitution of the Republic of South Africa and all other related legislations.",
